The paper deals with a pattern recognition task involving image processing and deep learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on offline signature verification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The proposed approach involves transfer learning, which is a popular technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for leveraging pre-trained models to improve performance on new tasks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of support vector machines (SVMs) for classification, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography (cs.CR).
